  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a dry, large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until charred all over then set aside for later</p>\n<p>Tip: Open a window or turn your extraction on, as this may get smoky!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-steak-fajitas-with-charred-chilli-salsa/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>chipotle paste</strong>, <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>dried chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cumin</strong> to a large plate with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and stir it all together</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>rump steaks</strong> to the plate and give everything a good mix up until fully coated in the spices</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-steak-fajitas-with-charred-chilli-salsa/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice most of the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and finely dice the rest</p>\n<p>Deseed the <strong>green pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-steak-fajitas-with-charred-chilli-salsa/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dice the <strong>tomatoes </strong>finely<strong> </strong>and add them to the bowl with the <strong>diced red onion</strong></p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>charred</strong> <strong>red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> finely (don't like spice? Deseed your chillies!) and add to the same bowl </p>\n<p>Add a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and the <strong>juice</strong> of the<strong> lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and stir it all together – this is your <strong>charred chilli salsa </strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-steak-fajitas-with-charred-chilli-salsa/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-high with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-steak-fajitas-with-charred-chilli-salsa/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion and pepper are cooking, heat another large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>For <strong>rare</strong>, cook for 2 min max on each side</p>\n<p>For <strong>medium-rare</strong>, cook for 2-3 min on each side</p>\n<p>For <strong>medium</strong>, cook for 3-4 min on each side</p>\n<p>Once done, remove them from the pan, finely slice, then add them to the peppers with any juices</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-steak-fajitas-with-charred-chilli-salsa/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the steaks are cooking, add the<strong> tortillas</strong> to a plate</p>\n<p>Put the plate in the<strong> microwave </strong>and cook for 1-2 min, or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-steak-fajitas-with-charred-chilli-salsa/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve up the <strong>tortillas</strong> topped with the <strong>sliced steak</strong>,<strong> peppers</strong> and<strong> onions</strong></p>\n<p>Drizzle over the <strong>soured cream</strong> and <strong>charred chilli salsa</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
